I didnâ€™t watch the Oscars this weekend, but Iâ€™ve been oddly emotional about it all week ğŸ¥º Of course what went down is really not OK, but as someone whoâ€™s experienced alopecia since her early 20â€™s (and often brought on from stress) the emotional toll of losing your hair is tough. Thereâ€™s lots of tears (usually in the shower as itâ€™s falling out) a feeling that your hairbrush is out to get you, and a ping of sadness every time you see loose hairs fall out - which happens what feels like every moment of every day. Iâ€™ve gone from a pixie cut, to long hair, to thickening extensions, to half of my hair, to short hair again, and have tried most â€œmagical hair serumsâ€ on the block.
